(44, 7, 49, 66, 3, 21, 21, 'my throne', 'Throne Imagery Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of a throne, with Acts 7:49 highlighting God''s sovereignty and Revelation 3:21 promising believers a place in that divine authority. This connection highlights the relationship between God''s throne and the promise of shared authority with the faithful.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 49, 11, 22, 19, 19, 'Heaven is my throne', 'Divine Sovereignty and Throne Imagery', 'This connection highlights the imagery of God on His throne in both passages. Acts 7:49 speaks of heaven as God''s throne, while 1 Kings 22:19 describes the Lord sitting on His throne, emphasizing His sovereignty.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 49, 40, 5, 34, 35, 'heaven is my throne, and earth is my footstool', 'Connection of Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of heaven as God''s throne and earth as His footstool, highlighting God''s sovereignty over all creation. This connection illustrates the divine authority and the futility of trying to confine God to a physical space.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
