(44, 7, 50, 44, 14, 15, 15, 'made all these things', 'Creation and Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize God''s role as the creator of all things. Acts 7:50 states that God''s hand made all things, while Acts 14:15 proclaims that the living God made heaven, earth, and the sea.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 50, 2, 20, 11, 11, 'Hath not my hand made all these things?', 'Creation and Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize God''s role as the creator. Acts 7:50 highlights that God''s hand made all things, while Exodus 20:11 details the creation of heaven and earth in six days.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 50, 19, 50, 9, 12, 'Hath not my hand made all these things?', 'Creation and Ownership of All', 'Both passages emphasize God''s sovereignty over creation. Acts 7:50 highlights God''s hand in making all things, while Psalms 50:9-12 declares that all beasts and the world belong to Him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 50, 23, 40, 28, 28, 'Hath not my hand made all these things?', 'Creation and Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize God''s role as Creator. Acts 7:50 highlights God''s hand in creation, while Isaiah 40:28 refers to God as the Creator of the ends of the earth.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
